.TH "ufshcd_scale_clks" 9 "ufshcd_scale_clks" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ufshcd_scale_clks \- scale up or scale down UFS controller clocks
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ufshcd_scale_clks
.BI "(struct ufs_hba *hba "  ","
.BI "bool scale_up "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hba" 12
per adapter instance
.IP "scale_up" 12
True if scaling up and false if scaling down
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 if successful
Returns < 0 for any other errors
